TRANSFIR clearly outperforms RLIE in quality. RLIE had a fundamental mathematical flaw in Eq. 2, inconsistent model attribution, missing ablations, and weak novelty. TRANSFIR has none of these fatal flaws — its weaknesses (zero-history fallback ambiguity, missing known-entity evaluation) are refinements rather than critical errors.

**Against 6.0-scored papers (lamda_malware, on_fragility_contamination):**  
